# Financial Organizer — Project Rules

## Designer workflow

I am a designer, not a developer. Always:

- Explain what you're doing in plain English before doing it
- Run all terminal commands yourself, never ask me to run them
- Stop and wait for my confirmation between major steps
- Never build more than what I asked for in one step
- If you hit an error, fix it before moving on
- Never push to GitHub without my explicit instruction

## Code rules

Always follow these without being asked:

- Use shadcn/ui components explicitly (Card, Button, Input, Badge, Separator) — never build custom divs when a shadcn component exists
- Use token-based spacing only: p-4, p-6, gap-4, gap-6 — never hardcode pixel values
- Mobile padding: p-4 (16px). Desktop padding: p-6 (24px)
- All cards use shadcn Card + CardContent with consistent internal padding
- Financial amounts always use text-3xl font-bold minimum
- Labels below amounts use text-sm text-muted-foreground
- All new Financial/ components must have a Storybook story
- Never add colors — grayscale only until brand confirmed
- When building from prototype, match UX flow exactly but redesign visually using our token system
- Never build more than one component per step without explicit approval
- Storybook: every component gets a story, organized under Tokens/ UI/ Layout/ Financial/ Pages/Mobile/ Pages/Desktop/
- Never create duplicate-looking stories — each story must be visually distinct
